    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> August 1850</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">My dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">Enclosed you will find&#44; put in a<lb/> poetical garb&#44; one of those interesting tales of which the Talmud abounds&#44;<lb/> and whose simplicity and moral tendency may have some beneficial<lb/> influence upon those of our people&#44; who have no access to venerated<lb/> books&#44; which <placeName>Israel</placeName> claims as an inheritance from their pious ancestors&#44;<lb/> and the preservation of which has cost them so much. If you think them<lb/> worth publishing in the Occident&#44; and agreeable to you&#44; I will use<lb/> my <sic>leasure</sic> moments for the purpose of furnishing you with a series<lb/> of them&#44; if possible&#59; one&#44; monthly. You can head them&#44; &#8220;Talmudical<lb/> Tales.&#8221; Please let me have an answer to this. What do you think<lb/> of <persName>Dr Wise&#39;s</persName> course&#63; By the by&#44; I know from good authority that<lb/> he could produce here no Diploma&#44; except the <add>Hebrew</add>. Upon which<lb/> the <placeName>Hazel Street</placeName> congregation&#44; with equal right doctorized <persName>Mr Eckman.</persName><lb/> It appears that the congregations&#44; not satisfied with the simple<lb/> Revd&#44; have assumed the authority of conferring Doctordom upon<lb/> any individual who happens to be their minister If a <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> bestowed by any Rabbi or Beth dun entitles the possessor to be<lb/> considered <hi rend="underline">Doctor of Divinity</hi>&#44; &#40;as <persName>Wise</persName> impertinently signed his name in the last<lb/> occident&#41; we may <hi rend="underline">all</hi> assume it. No Rabbi in <placeName>Germany</placeName>&#44; <placeName>England</placeName>&#44; etc.<lb/> is Doctor of divinity&#44; nor do they assume the power of conferring it<lb/> upon others. <persName>Drs Adler</persName>&#44; <persName>Frankel</persName>&#44; <persName>Geiger Raphael</persName> <sic>ect</sic>&#44; are all Doctors of<lb/> Phylosophy. If matters remain so&#44; <persName>Dr Wise</persName> as well as the <placeName>Hazel Street</placeName><lb/> congregation will soon fabricate sufficient Doctors to colonize the<lb/> world</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The cause of orthodoxy is fast declining in this city.<lb/> <persName>Pozenanskis</persName> resignation and <persName>Eckman&#39;s</persName> pretending to be a<lb/> strict orthodox Jew&#44; have charged affairs considerably. Many<lb/> of those who were formerly Champions in our cause have found&#44;<lb/> after mature reflection&#44; that all their zeal was based on<lb/> party spirit&#44; and by no means on true religious principles.<lb/> Many say now <add>Hebrew</add>. The fact is&#44; that<lb/> infidelism and indifference have taken such root here&#44; that&#44; I<lb/> apprehend they will never be <sic>erazed</sic>. <persName>Pozenanski</persName> left a<lb/> deep&#44; venomous string behind him which is calculated to poison<lb/> the latest generations. You can form an idea of the <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> orthodoxy&#44; when ever <add>Hebrew</add> is neglected. Our Shochet is an old man&#44;<lb/> whose nervous temperament&#44; together an occasional attack<lb/> of Rheumatism causes his hands to tremble considerably&#44; which<lb/> according to our Law&#44; disqualifies him from being <add>Hebrew</add> and yet<lb/> with all my efforts&#44; I could not induce the congregation even<lb/> to have him examined&#44; although he has not been examined for<lb/> <hi rend="underline">many</hi> years&#44; and has had almost every year a severe spell<lb/> of sickness. I know he is incapable. Besides&#44; he never examines the<lb/> lungs by sight&#44; he is satisfied by putting his hands in the animal<lb/> and declaring <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; a proceeding which is entirely against<lb/> law&#44; as it is an impossibility for any man&#44; no matter how proficient<lb/> he may be&#44; to declare an animal to be <add>Hebrew</add> without examining it<lb/> closely&#44; <add>Hebrew</add>. Many other things have transpired lately<lb/> which convince me that Orthodoxy is loosing ground rapidly&#44;<lb/> And that the congregation Shearit Israel may soon die an<lb/> untimely death. I think nothing can save it&#44; and if matters<lb/> remain as they are&#44; and as they will probably be&#44; my stay here will be</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>of short duration. I hope that your affairs will terminate<lb/> more satisfactorily than you anticipated&#44; at least this the opinion<lb/> of your friends here. It is at the same time hoped&#44; and expected<lb/> that you will yield to conciliatory measures. Hoping that<lb/> this may reach you in the enjoyment of good health and content<lb/>ment&#44; and wishing you <add>Hebrew</add> I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">Yrs Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Jacob Rosenfeld</persName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p>The</p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          
